<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
<title>Genomics | PanorOmics</title>

<style>
*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}

body{
  background:#020817;
  color:white;
  font-family:Inter,Arial,sans-serif;
  overflow-x:hidden;
}

.page{
  padding:72px 7% 42px;
}

.back{
  color:#3b82f6;
  text-decoration:none;
  font-size:.92rem;
  font-weight:700;
}

.hero{
  margin-top:34px;
  display:grid;
  grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
  gap:34px;
  align-items:center;
}

h1{
  font-size:clamp(2.3rem,4vw,4rem);
  line-height:.98;
  letter-spacing:-.05em;
}

h1 span{color:#3b82f6}

p{
  margin-top:18px;
  color:#cbd5e1;
  font-size:.95rem;
  line-height:1.65;
  max-width:680px;
}

.video-box,
.image-box{
  border-radius:22px;
  overflow:hidden;
  border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.14);
  box-shadow:0 0 50px rgba(37,99,235,.12);
}
.infographic{
  width:100vw;
  margin-left:calc(50% - 50vw);
  margin-top:32px;
}

.infographic img{
  width:100%;
  display:block;
  border-radius:24px;
}
video,img{
  width:100%;
  display:block;
}

.section{
  padding:38px 0;
}

h2{
  font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3vw,2.6rem);
  margin-bottom:18px;
}

.grid{
  display:grid;
  grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(230px,1fr));
  gap:18px;
  margin-top:24px;
}

.card{
  background:rgba(8,15,35,.72);
  border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.12);
  border-radius:20px;
  padding:20px;
}

.card h3{
  color:#3b82f6;
  margin-bottom:10px;
  font-size:1.1rem;
}

.card p{
  margin-top:0;
  font-size:.9rem;
  color:#94a3b8;
}

@media(max-width:900px){
  .hero{grid-template-columns:1fr}
  .page{padding:64px 20px 36px}
}
</style>
</head>

<body>

<main class="page">

  <a class="back" href="/">← Back to PanorOmics</a>

  <section class="hero">

    <div>
      <h1>Genomics: <span>Decoding the Blueprint of Life</span></h1>

      <p>
        Genomics investigates the complete set of genetic information encoded
        within DNA. Through sequencing, variant discovery, computational biology,
        and systems-level analysis, genomics enables precision medicine,
        disease discovery, and biological understanding across individuals and populations.
      </p>
    </div>

   <div class="video-box">
  <video autoplay muted loop playsinline>
    <source src="/genomics-cinematic-v1.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
  </video>
</div>

  </section>

  <section class="section">

  <h2>What is Genomics?</h2>

  <div class="infographic">
    <img
      src="/2_Genomics.png"
      alt="Genomics overview infographic"
    />
  </div>

</section>
  <section class="section">

    <h2>Core Areas</h2>

    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card"><h3>Genome Sequencing</h3><p>Reading DNA information at scale.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Variant Calling</h3><p>Identifying genetic differences linked to biology and disease.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Precision Medicine</h3><p>Connecting genomic variation to diagnosis and treatment.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Population Genomics</h3><p>Studying genetic diversity across groups and populations.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>AI Genomics</h3><p>Using computational models to interpret genomic complexity.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Systems Biology</h3><p>Integrating genomics with other omics layers.</p></div>
    </div>

  </section>

</main>

</body>
</html>
